All Classes

Class Summary 
Class Description
Ballot
Contains the information related to an individual ballot and provides methods to retrieve information about the choices made on that ballot during the course of an election.
BallotFactory
The class BallotFactory is responsible for taking input files as a File array from the Main Window and return the arraylist of total number of ballots inside a given list of files.
BallotFileChooser
A file chooser interface which allows a user to navigate the file system and select either ballot files or a directory.
Candidate
Contains the information used to describe a particular candidate in an election and provides methods to facilitate the distribution and redistribution of ballots during the course of an election.
ElectionController
The class ElectionController is responsible for controlling both PluralityController and STVController elections and must be connected with MainWindow class.
HelpWindow
A dialog window which presents the user with instructions to help them use SVS.
MainWindow
The primary interface through which a user interacts with SVS.
PluralityController
This class is in charge of running the Plurality Algorithm on the ballots and candidates provided by the user.
STVDroopController
This class is in charge of running the Droop Quota Algorithm on the ballots and candidates that the user provides.
SVS
The class that contains the entry point for SVS.
